                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             ===Issue===                                                                                            
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Summary                                                                                             
                                                                                                                                    
                             A libFuzzer run terminated with an ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout message. The fuzzer did                 
                             not produce a crash or memory error but instead exceeded its execution time limit                      
                             while exercising the target code through the provided harness.                                         
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Description                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                    
                             - Issue Overview                                                                                       
                               The fuzzer (libFuzzer) stopped testing due to a timeout condition: the target code                   
                             did not complete processing of an input within the allotted time. No crash, memory                     
                             corruption, or sanitizer alert was reportedonly a timeout.                                            
                                                                                                                                    
                             - Vulnerability Type                                                                                   
                               The issue report does not specify a particular vulnerability class. A timeout may                    
                             point toward performance degradation or potential denial-of-service behavior under                     
                             pathological inputs, but no explicit vulnerability type is mentioned in the issue                      
                             text.                                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                    
                             - Key Observations and Findings                                                                        
                                The fuzzer reached its internal time limit without completing the test case.                       
                                There are no stack traces, sanitizer logs, or error codes beyond the timeout                       
                             message.                                                                                               
                                The harness merely feeds inputs into the target code and is not identified as the                  
                             root cause; it is an entry point for fuzz testing.                                                     
                                No memory safety bugs (use-after-free, buffer overflow), nor crashes, were                         
                             detectedonly an execution hang or overly long runtime.                                                
                                                                                                                                    
                             - Code Areas for Investigation                                                                         
                               To understand why the fuzzer timed out, the following parts of the codebase should                   
                             be reviewed:                                                                                           
                               1. Fuzz Target Functions                                                                             
                                   Entry points called by the harness.                                                             
                                   Any loops, recursive routines, or state machines that may fail to terminate                     
                             promptly.                                                                                              
                               2. Input-Processing Modules                                                                          
                                   Parsers, deserializers, or interpreters that handle untrusted or malformed                      
                             data.                                                                                                  
                                   Large-data buffering or streaming logic that might block.                                       
                               3. External Dependencies                                                                             
                                   Calls to I/O subsystems (file, network, database) which could block under                       
                             certain inputs.                                                                                        
                                   Third-party libraries invoked by the fuzz target.                                               
                               4. Resource Management                                                                               
                                   Allocation patterns that might trigger long GC pauses or excessive memory use.                  
                                   Synchronization constructs (locks, condition variables) that might deadlock or                  
                             stall.                                                                                                 
                               5. Time-Sensitive Logic                                                                              
                                   Any deliberate sleeping, waiting, or polling loops influenced by input                          
                             contents.                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             A thorough review of these areas will help characterize the precise code paths leading                 
                             to the timeout and provide a comprehensive view of where performance or termination                    
                             guarantees may be lacking.

                             ===Patch Result===                                                                                     
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             ===Issue===                                                                                            
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Summary                                                                                             
                             The projects PDF parser is being fuzzed with libFuzzer and consistently triggers a                    
                             timeout (`ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`). To address excessive scanning in                                
                             `BruteForceParser`, a patch was introduced that defines a `MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH`                     
                             limit (10 000 000 bytes) and breaks out of the bruteforce loop when that threshold is                 
                             exceeded. After applying this patch, the fuzzer still reports the same timeout error,                  
                             indicating the change did not prevent longrunning parsing loops.                                      
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Description                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                    
                             Initial Issue                                                                                          
                             - During fuzzing with libFuzzer, the process hangs or exceeds the allowed execution                    
                             time on certain inputs.                                                                                
                             - The only log message is `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`, with no stack trace or                          
                             exception reported.                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                    
                             Important Observations                                                                                 
                             - The timeout points toward a tight loop or extensive scanning routine in the parser                   
                             code.                                                                                                  
                             - No direct evidence in the harness indicates a crash or memory leakonly excessive                    
                             runtime.                                                                                               
                             - The absence of logging or instrumentation around the timeout makes it difficult to                   
                             pinpoint which parsing phase is responsible.                                                           
                                                                                                                                    
                             Patch Attempt                                                                                          
                             - File modified:                                                                                       
                             `pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.java`                               
                             - Inserted constant:                                                                                   
                                   private static final long MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH = 10000000L;                                    
                             - In method `bfSearchForObjects()`, directly after reading each byte and incrementing                  
                             `currentOffset`, added a check:                                                                        
                                   if (currentOffset - originOffset > MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH) {                                     
                                       break;                                                                                       
                                   }                                                                                                
                             - The intent was to cap the brute-force search window and exit early if too many bytes                 
                             have been scanned without finding an object marker.                                                    
                                                                                                                                    
                             Resulting Log After Patch                                                                              
                             - Fuzzer output remains:                                                                               
                                   ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                        
                             - No new error messages or early exits are observed, implying the loop still runs                      
                             longer than the fuzzers timeout threshold or other code paths are causing delays.                     
                                                                                                                                    
                             Areas for Further Investigation                                                                        
                             - `BruteForceParser.bfSearchForLastEOFMarker()` and its performance characteristics;                   
                             if it scans large sections unbounded.                                                                  
                             - The overall control flow in `BruteForceParser.bfSearchForObjects()`, including any                   
                             nested loops or recursive calls that may exceed time limits.                                           
                             - Interaction with `BaseParser.isWhitespace()` and `parser.isString(OBJ_MARKER)`:                      
                             whether these checks are efficient or invoke expensive operations.                                     
                             - I/O operations on `source` (seek/read)  ensure no blocking or redundant reads                       
                             occur.                                                                                                 
                             - Other parsing routines outside `BruteForceParser` that may be triggered after the                    
                             bruteforce phase and contribute to the timeout.                                                       
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                   
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                                         
                             <issue>                                                                                                
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             </issue>                                                                                               
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Additional Issue Log                                                                                
                             Here is the additional issue log after the last patch attempt:                                         
                             <additional_issue>                                                                                     
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             </additional_issue>                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Notes                                                                                               
                             - All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous                     
                             patches if needed.                                                                                     
                             - If multiple different issues are present, all the issues must be resolved in a                       
                             single patch attempt.                                                                                  
                             - Try different approaches to resolve the issues.

                             527:        long originOffset = source.getPosition();                                                  
                             528:        source.seek(MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET);                                                        
                             529:        long tempMarker = findString(EOF_MARKER);

                             533:            {

                             137:        long lastObjectId = Long.MIN_VALUE;

                             141:        char[] endobjRemainingString = "bj".toCharArray();                                         
                             142:        boolean endOfObjFound = false;                                                             
                             143:        do                                                                                         
                             144:        {                                                                                          
                             145:            source.seek(currentOffset);                                                            
                             146:            int nextChar = source.read();                                                          
                             147:            currentOffset++;                                                                       
                             148:            if (BaseParser.isWhitespace(nextChar) && parser.isString(OBJ_MARKER))                  
                             149:            {                                                                                      
                             150:                long tempOffset = currentOffset - 2;                                               
                             151:                source.seek(tempOffset);                                                           
                             152:                int genID = source.peek();                                                         
                             153:                // is the next char a digit?                                                       
                             154:                if (BaseParser.isDigit(genID))                                                     
                             155:                {                                                                                  
                             156:                    genID -= 48;                                                                   
                             157:                    tempOffset--;

                             159:                    if (parser.isWhitespace())                                                     
                             160:                    {

                             parser.isWhitespace())                                                                                 
                             162:                        {                                                                          
                             163:                            source.seek(--tempOffset);                                             
                             164:                        }

                             166:                        while (tempOffset > MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET &&

                             167:                        {                                                                          
                             168:                            source.seek(--tempOffset);                                             
                             169:                            objectIDFound = true;                                                  
                             170:                        }                                                                          
                             171:                        if (objectIDFound)                                                         
                             172:                        {                                                                          
                             173:                            source.read();                                                         
                             174:                            long objectId = parser.readObjectNumber();

                             176:                            {

                             178:                                bfSearchCOSObjectKeyOffsets.put(                                   
                             179:                                        new COSObjectKey(lastObjectId, lastGenID),                 
                             lastObjOffset);                                                                                        
                             180:                            }                                                                      
                             181:                            lastObjectId = objectId;                                               
                             182:                            lastGenID = genID;                                                     
                             183:                            lastObjOffset = tempOffset + 1;                                        
                             184:                            currentOffset += OBJ_MARKER.length - 1;                                
                             185:                            endOfObjFound = false;                                                 
                             186:                        }                                                                          
                             187:                    }                                                                              
                             188:                }                                                                                  
                             189:            }                                                                                      
                             190:            // check for "endo" as abbreviation for "endobj", as the pdf may be                    
                             cut off                                                                                                
                             191:            // in the middle of the keyword, see PDFBOX-3936.                                      
                             192:            // We could possibly implement a more intelligent algorithm if                         
                             necessary                                                                                              
                             193:            else if (nextChar == 'e' && parser.isString(endobjString))                             
                             194:            {

                             196:                source.seek(currentOffset);

                             204:                    endOfObjFound = true;

                             604:                                        length++;                                                  
                             605:                                    }                                                              
                             606:                                    if (length > 0)                                                
                             607:                                    {                                                              
                             ```

                             1239:     * @throws IOException If there is an error reading from the stream.                          
                             1240:     */                                                                                           
                             1241:    protected boolean isWhitespace() throws IOException                                           
                             1242:    {                                                                                             
                             1243:        return isWhitespace(source.peek());                                                       
                             1244:    }                                                                                             
                             1245:                                                                                                  
                             1246:    /**                                                                                           
                             1247:     * This will tell if a character is whitespace or not.  These values are                      
                             1248:     * specified in table 1 (page 12) of ISO 32000-1:2008.                                        
                             1249:     * @param c The character to check against whitespace                                         
                             1250:     * @return true if the character is a whitespace character.                                   
                             1251:     */                                                                                           
                             1252:    protected static boolean isWhitespace( int c )                                                
                             1253:    {                                                                                             
                             1254:        switch (c)                                                                                
                             1255:        {                                                                                         
                             1256:        case ASCII_NULL:                                                                          
                             1257:        case ASCII_TAB:                                                                           
                             1258:        case ASCII_FF:                                                                            
                             1259:        case ASCII_LF:                                                                            
                             1260:        case ASCII_CR:                                                                            
                             1261:        case ASCII_SPACE:                                                                         
                             1262:            return true;                                                                          
                             1263:        default:                                                                                  
                             1264:            return false;                                                                         
                             1265:        }                                                                                         
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             </code_snippets>                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                        
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                    
                             To prevent unbounded, time-consuming scans in all brute-force routines (not just                       
                             bfSearchForObjects), we must enforce a universal cap on byte scanning. The optimal                     
                             approach is:                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                    
                             1. Introduce a single MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH constant at class level:                                  
                                 private static final long MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH = 10_000_000L;                                   
                                                                                                                                    
                             2. Modify the low-level findString(...) routine to abort after scanning                                
                             MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH bytes:                                                                          
                                a. At method start, record long startPos = source.getPosition().                                    
                                b. In the main whileloop (per byte read), compute scanned = source.getPosition()                  
                             startPos.                                                                                              
                                c. If scanned > MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH, immediately return 1, indicating not                      
                             found within limit.                                                                                   
                                d. This bounds every invocation of findString (used by EOF, xref table, xref                        
                             stream, obj stream searches).                                                                          
                                                                                                                                    
                             3. Tighten bfSearchForObjects itself to avoid manual full-file walks:                                  
                                a. After computing originOffset = MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET, compute long                               
                             searchLimitOffset = originOffset + MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH.                                             
                                b. Change the do/while loop condition from                                                          
                                     } while (currentOffset < lastEOFMarker && !parser.isEOF());                                    
                                   to                                                                                               
                                     } while (currentOffset < lastEOFMarker                                                         
                                              && currentOffset < searchLimitOffset                                                  
                                              && !parser.isEOF());                                                                  
                                c. Remove or leave the inner if (currentOffset  originOffset >                                    
                             MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH) break; since its now redundant.                                              
                                d. Log at DEBUG level when the cap is hit, to aid future profiling:                                 
                                     LOG.debug("Brute-force object search reached {} bytes; aborting.",                             
                             MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH);                                                                               
                                                                                                                                    
                             4. For all other brute-force search routines (bfSearchForLastEOFMarker,                                
                             bfSearchForObjStreamOffsets, bfSearchForXRefTables, bfSearchForXRefStreams):                           
                                 They all invoke findString(...) under the hood, so the capped findString prevents                 
                             them from scanning past the limit. No further per-method changes are necessary.                        
                                                                                                                                    
                             5. Preserve existing logic:                                                                            
                                 findString returns 1 on timeout, causing callers to treat marker not found and                 
                             proceed or abort gracefully.                                                                           
                                 No external APIs, harness code, utility functions, or tests are modified.                         
                                 Existing parsing logic (whitespace checks, object number parsing, etc.) remains                   
                             intact.                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                    
                             Why this works:                                                                                        
                              The original timeout stemmed from full-file scans in findString and manual loops                     
                             that ignored the MAX limit. By capping every byte-by-byte scan globally at a                           
                             reasonable threshold, we prevent the fuzzer from entering long loops.                                  
                              Limiting findString eliminates repeated multi-MB scans in EOF, xref, obj-stream                      
                             searches without altering their higher-level workflows.                                                
                              Tightening bfSearchForObjects bounds its manual search loop, so it cannot run past                   
                             MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH bytes even if lastEOFMarker is infinite.                                        
                              Tests that expect full-file parsing on small documents are unaffected; production                    
                             code still finds markers if they appear within the first 10 MB beyond the search                       
                             offset.                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                    
                             Potential side effects & mitigation:                                                                   
                              Very large, valid PDFs with markers >10 MB apart will be truncated by the cap. If                    
                             this is a concern for real-world parsing (not fuzzing), consider exposing the limit                    
                             via a system property or parser configuration flag (e.g., setMaxBruteForceSearch()) to                 
                             disable or raise the cap in production. This extension does not affect the fuzzing                     
                             harness and can be added later if needed.                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             References:                                                                                            
                              Similar caps are sometimes applied in XML or HTML parsers to prevent BOM scans from                  
                             running past a threshold.                                                                              
                              In this codebase, MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH was already used in bfSearchForObjects;                     
                             weve generalized it to all findStringdriven loops.                                                   
                                                                                                                                    
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                        
                             ===Evaluation End===

                             ===Issue===                                                                                            
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Summary                                                                                             
                             The initial issue reported by libFuzzer was a persistent timeout when running the                      
                             PDFBox parser under fuzz testing. In response, a patch was introduced that defines an                  
                             upper bound (`MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH = 10,000,000` bytes) on two brute-force search                    
                             loops: one in `bfSearchForObjects()` (limiting the offset scan) and one in                             
                             `findString(char[])` (aborting after reading the threshold). After applying the patch,                 
                             the libFuzzer run still ends in a timeout with no crash or new diagnostic information.                 
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Description                                                                                         
                             1. Initial Issue                                                                                       
                                - The fuzzer invocation terminates with `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`.                                
                                - No stack trace or error message beyond the timeout is emitted.                                    
                                - The failure indicates that the code under test exceeded the allotted execution                    
                             time without exposing a crash or hang location in the parser.                                          
                                                                                                                                    
                             2. Observations & Findings                                                                             
                                - The PDF parser uses brute-force scanning to locate PDF objects and markers (e.g.,                 
                             endobj, cross-reference tables).                                                                     
                                - Those loops (in `BruteForceParser.bfSearchForObjects()` and `findString`) can                     
                             traverse large portions of a PDF stream, which under fuzzing may lead to excessively                   
                             long scans.                                                                                            
                                - The harness itself simply feeds arbitrary data to `PDFParser` and is not altered                  
                             by this patch. It remains an entry point rather than the root cause.                                   
                                                                                                                                    
                             3. Patch Attempt                                                                                       
                                - A new constant was added at the top of `BruteForceParser`:                                        
                                  ```java                                                                                           
                                  private static final long MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH = 10000000L;                                     
                                  ```                                                                                               
                                - In `bfSearchForObjects()`, the loop condition was modified to:                                    
                                  ```diff                                                                                           
                                  - } while (currentOffset < lastEOFMarker && !parser.isEOF());                                     
                                  + } while (currentOffset < lastEOFMarker                                                          
                                  +        && currentOffset < searchLimitOffset                                                     
                                  +        && !parser.isEOF());                                                                     
                                  ```                                                                                               
                                  where `searchLimitOffset = originOffset + MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH`.                                
                                - In `findString(char[] string)`, a position check was added before each byte                       
                             compare:                                                                                               
                                  ```java                                                                                           
                                  long startPos = source.getPosition();                                                             
                                  while (readChar != -1) {                                                                          
                                      if (source.getPosition() - startPos > MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH) {                               
                                          LOG.debug("Brute-force findString reached {} bytes; aborting.",                           
                             MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SEARCH);                                                                               
                                          return -1L;                                                                               
                                      }                                                                                             
                                      // existing match logic...                                                                    
                                  }                                                                                                 
                                  ```                                                                                               
                                - After recompiling and rerunning libFuzzer, the same timeout error occurred.                       
                                                                                                                                    
                             4. Areas for Further Investigation                                                                     
                                - Other scanning or parsing loops in `BruteForceParser` (e.g., cross-reference                      
                             search, object header identification) to see if they similarly lack bounds.                            
                                - Any recursive or nested parsing routines that may re-invoke the brute-force                       
                             methods without respecting the limit.                                                                  
                                - Interaction between `source.getPosition()` and the underlying `RandomAccessRead`                  
                             implementation to confirm offset calculations.                                                         
                                - Overall control flow in `PDFParser` to identify code paths that could block or                    
                             spin without yielding.                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                    
                             No cause is confirmed at this stage; the patch enforced a local byte-limit but the                     
                             timeout remains. Continuous profiling or additional logging in these routines may be                   
                             required to locate the exact performance bottleneck.                                                   
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                   
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                                         
                             <issue>                                                                                                
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             </issue>                                                                                               
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Additional Issue Log                                                                                
                             Here is the additional issue log after the last patch attempt:                                         
                             <additional_issue>                                                                                     
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             </additional_issue>                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Notes                                                                                               
                             - All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous                     
                             patches if needed.                                                                                     
                             - If multiple different issues are present, all the issues must be resolved in a                       
                             single patch attempt.                                                                                  
                             - Try different approaches to resolve the issues.

                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.java:524-560                         
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             524:    private long bfSearchForLastEOFMarker() throws IOException                                     
                             525:    {                                                                                              
                             526:        long lastEOFMarker = -1;                                                                   
                             527:        long originOffset = source.getPosition();                                                  
                             528:        source.seek(MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET);                                                        
                             529:        long tempMarker = findString(EOF_MARKER);                                                  
                             530:        while (tempMarker != -1)                                                                   
                             531:        {                                                                                          
                             532:            try                                                                                    
                             533:            {                                                                                      
                             534:                // check if the following data is some valid pdf content                           
                             535:                // which most likely indicates that the pdf is linearized,                         
                             536:                // updated or just cut off somewhere in the middle                                 
                             537:                parser.skipSpaces();                                                               
                             538:                if (!parser.isString(XREF_TABLE))                                                  
                             539:                {                                                                                  
                             540:                    parser.readObjectNumber();                                                     
                             541:                    parser.readGenerationNumber();                                                 
                             542:                }                                                                                  
                             543:            }                                                                                      
                             544:            catch (IOException exception)                                                          
                             545:            {                                                                                      
                             546:                // save the EOF marker as the following data is most likely some                   
                             garbage                                                                                                
                             547:                LOG.debug("An exception occurred during brute force for last EOF -                 
                             ignoring",                                                                                             
                             548:                        exception);                                                                
                             549:                lastEOFMarker = tempMarker;                                                        
                             550:            }                                                                                      
                             551:            tempMarker = findString(EOF_MARKER);                                                   
                             552:        }                                                                                          
                             553:        source.seek(originOffset);                                                                 
                             554:        // no EOF marker found                                                                     
                             555:        if (lastEOFMarker == -1)                                                                   
                             556:        {                                                                                          
                             557:            lastEOFMarker = Long.MAX_VALUE;                                                        
                             558:        }                                                                                          
                             559:        return lastEOFMarker;                                                                      
                             560:    }                                                                                              
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.java:780-809                         
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             780:    private long findString(char[] string) throws IOException                                      
                             781:    {                                                                                              
                             782:        long position = -1L;                                                                       
                             783:        int stringLength = string.length;                                                          
                             784:        int counter = 0;                                                                           
                             785:        int readChar = source.read();                                                              
                             786:        while (readChar != -1)                                                                     
                             787:        {                                                                                          
                             788:            if (readChar == string[counter])                                                       
                             789:            {                                                                                      
                             790:                if (counter == 0)                                                                  
                             791:                {                                                                                  
                             792:                    position = source.getPosition() - 1;                                           
                             793:                }                                                                                  
                             794:                counter++;                                                                         
                             795:                if (counter == stringLength)                                                       
                             796:                {                                                                                  
                             797:                    return position;                                                               
                             798:                }                                                                                  
                             799:            }                                                                                      
                             800:            else if (counter > 0)                                                                  
                             801:            {                                                                                      
                             802:                counter = 0;                                                                       
                             803:                position = -1L;                                                                    
                             804:                continue;                                                                          
                             805:            }                                                                                      
                             806:            readChar = source.read();                                                              
                             807:        }                                                                                          
                             808:        return position;                                                                           
                             809:    }                                                                                              
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.java:132-208                         
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             132:    private void bfSearchForObjects() throws IOException                                           
                             133:    {                                                                                              
                             134:        long lastEOFMarker = bfSearchForLastEOFMarker();                                           
                             135:        long originOffset = source.getPosition();                                                  
                             136:        long currentOffset = MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET;                                                
                             137:        long lastObjectId = Long.MIN_VALUE;                                                        
                             138:        int lastGenID = Integer.MIN_VALUE;                                                         
                             139:        long lastObjOffset = Long.MIN_VALUE;                                                       
                             140:        char[] endobjString = "ndo".toCharArray();                                                 
                             141:        char[] endobjRemainingString = "bj".toCharArray();                                         
                             142:        boolean endOfObjFound = false;                                                             
                             143:        do                                                                                         
                             144:        {                                                                                          
                             145:            source.seek(currentOffset);                                                            
                             146:            int nextChar = source.read();                                                          
                             147:            currentOffset++;                                                                       
                             148:            if (BaseParser.isWhitespace(nextChar) && parser.isString(OBJ_MARKER))                  
                             149:            {                                                                                      
                             150:                long tempOffset = currentOffset - 2;                                               
                             151:                source.seek(tempOffset);                                                           
                             152:                int genID = source.peek();                                                         
                             153:                // is the next char a digit?                                                       
                             154:                if (BaseParser.isDigit(genID))                                                     
                             155:                {                                                                                  
                             156:                    genID -= 48;                                                                   
                             157:                    tempOffset--;                                                                  
                             158:                    source.seek(tempOffset);                                                       
                             159:                    if (parser.isWhitespace())                                                     
                             160:                    {                                                                              
                             161:                        while (tempOffset > MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET &&                               
                             parser.isWhitespace())                                                                                 
                             162:                        {                                                                          
                             163:                            source.seek(--tempOffset);                                             
                             164:                        }                                                                          
                             165:                        boolean objectIDFound = false;                                             
                             166:                        while (tempOffset > MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET &&                               
                             parser.isDigit())                                                                                      
                             167:                        {                                                                          
                             168:                            source.seek(--tempOffset);                                             
                             169:                            objectIDFound = true;                                                  
                             170:                        }                                                                          
                             171:                        if (objectIDFound)                                                         
                             172:                        {                                                                          
                             173:                            source.read();                                                         
                             174:                            long objectId = parser.readObjectNumber();                             
                             175:                            if (lastObjOffset > 0)                                                 
                             176:                            {                                                                      
                             177:                                // add the former object ID only if there was a                    
                             subsequent object ID                                                                                   
                             178:                                bfSearchCOSObjectKeyOffsets.put(                                   
                             179:                                        new COSObjectKey(lastObjectId, lastGenID),                 
                             lastObjOffset);                                                                                        
                             180:                            }                                                                      
                             181:                            lastObjectId = objectId;                                               
                             182:                            lastGenID = genID;                                                     
                             183:                            lastObjOffset = tempOffset + 1;                                        
                             184:                            currentOffset += OBJ_MARKER.length - 1;                                
                             185:                            endOfObjFound = false;                                                 
                             186:                        }                                                                          
                             187:                    }                                                                              
                             188:                }                                                                                  
                             189:            }                                                                                      
                             190:            // check for "endo" as abbreviation for "endobj", as the pdf may be                    
                             cut off                                                                                                
                             191:            // in the middle of the keyword, see PDFBOX-3936.                                      
                             192:            // We could possibly implement a more intelligent algorithm if                         
                             necessary                                                                                              
                             193:            else if (nextChar == 'e' && parser.isString(endobjString))                             
                             194:            {                                                                                      
                             195:                currentOffset += endobjString.length;                                              
                             196:                source.seek(currentOffset);                                                        
                             197:                if (parser.isEOF())                                                                
                             198:                {                                                                                  
                             199:                    endOfObjFound = true;                                                          
                             200:                }                                                                                  
                             201:                else if (parser.isString(endobjRemainingString))                                   
                             202:                {                                                                                  
                             203:                    currentOffset += endobjRemainingString.length;                                 
                             204:                    endOfObjFound = true;                                                          
                             205:                }                                                                                  
                             206:            }                                                                                      
                             207:        } while (currentOffset < lastEOFMarker && !parser.isEOF());                                
                             208:        if ((lastEOFMarker < Long.MAX_VALUE || endOfObjFound) && lastObjOffset >                   
                             0)                                                                                                     
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>

                             604:                                        length++;                                                  
                             605:                                    }                                                              
                             606:                                    if (length > 0)                                                
                             607:                                    {
